      <body>This line doesn't look right at all:

@@@ ruby
ids.inject([]) {|m, o| m &lt;&lt; (o.kind_of?(Range) ? o.to_a : o)}.flatten.compact.uniq
@@@

And why special-case Ranges? Why not accept anything that has a `to_a` method?</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This line doesn't look right at all:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code class=
&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;ids.inject([]) {|m, o| m &amp;lt;&amp;lt; (o.kind_of?(Range) ? o.to_a : o)}.flatten.compact.uniq&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And why special-case Ranges? Why not accept anything that has a
&lt;code&gt;to_a&lt;/code&gt; method?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
