      <body>We could *almost* do

@@@
ids = ids.map(&amp;:to_a).flatten.compact.uniq
@@@

The problem is that under 1.9, Fixnum doesn't have a to_a. So the code is more about special-casing Fixnum. Not clear to me that picking up everything that has to_a is the right answer - we need a specific thing, an array of integers, no?</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We could &lt;em&gt;almost&lt;/em&gt; do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;ids = ids.map(&amp;amp;:to_a).flatten.compact.uniq&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The problem is that under 1.9, Fixnum doesn't have a to_a. So
the code is more about special-casing Fixnum. Not clear to me that
picking up everything that has to_a is the right answer - we need a
specific thing, an array of integers, no?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
